                "#doi:10.1103/PhysRevC.100.054601"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "FACILITY": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "facility": [
                  "CYCLO"
                ],
                "institute": "3CPRIMP"
              },
              "free_text": [
                " Heavy Ion Research Facility in",
                "                Lanzhou (HIRFL)"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "INC-SOURCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The collimated 9Be beam with an initial energy of",
                "50.4 MeV was delivered by HIRFL. The average beam",
                "current was about 13 enA."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Five targets of 89Y, each with 197Au backing of about",
                "1 mg/cm2."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ANALYSIS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The authors assumed the number of the products escaped",
                " from the upstream Au foil (30% of the products) is",
                " equal the number of the products escaped to the",
                " downstream Au foil.",
                "The radioactivity of the first foil is much lower than",
                " the other four foils due to this reason and its",
                " effective beam energy is not given in Table II."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "STTA",
                "ACTIV",
                "GSPEC"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " A stacked foil online activation",
                "followed by an offline gamma-ray spectroscopy method.",
                "After the 12 hours irradiation, the activity of the",
                "targets was measured offline using five HPGe detector",
                "groups in a separate laboratory."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "BCINT"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The beam flux was calculated by the total",
                "charge collected in the Faraday cup placed behind the",
                "targets using a high precision current integrator.",
                "The Faraday cup was biased with a negative 400 V",
                "electrode on the collector to repel the secondary",
                "electrons."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SIBAR"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " During the bombardments, two silicon surface-",
                "barrier detectors were placed at +-30 deg to the beam",
                "for monitoring the elastic scattering of the beam",
                "particles by an Au foil placed upstream from the",
                "target stack."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "HPGE"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Each HPGe detector group consisted of two HPGe",
                "detectors positioned 180 deg to each other, where",
                "single gamma-ray and gamma-gamma coincidence",
                "measurements could be performed simultaneously. The",
                "Ge crystal part of each detector was surrounded by a",
                "Pb annular cylinder of 3 cm thickness to reduce",
                "background from natural radioactivity. In addition,",
                "Pb blocks of 6 cm thickness were inserted between",
                "each adjacent detector group to shield gamma-rays",
                "from neighboring targets. The absolute efficiency of",
                "the detectors was determined using a set of activity",
                "calibrated radioactive sources (60Co, 133Ba, and",
                "152Eu) mounted with the same geometry as the targets."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ERR-ANALYS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "heading": "ERR-T",
                "minimum_value": null,
                "maximum_value": null,
                "correlation_property": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " The errors of the deduced cross sections are",
